  "text": "Similar to [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , and [CITATION_3] , we also make the connection with flows on the links of a wireless network G and the link scheduling. We give both a necessary and a sufficient condition on the link flows such that an interference-free link scheduling is feasible. Recall that we use fðeÞ and cðeÞ to denote the load and the capacity of a link e, respectively. From Lemma 6 and Theorem 7, it follows that: The proofs of the above theorems are similar to those of [CITATION_4] , [CITATION_5] , and [CITATION_6] for other interference and networking models, and are, thus, omitted here.",
